  <front>
    <title>COPS Usage for MPLS/Traffic Engineering 
</title>
    <seriesInfo name="Internet-Draft" value="draft-franr-mpls-cops-00"/>
    <author initials="F." surname="Reichmeyer" fullname="Francis Reichmeyer">
      <organization>IPHighway</organization>
    </author>
    <author initials="S." surname="Wright" fullname="Steve Wright"/>
    <author initials="M." surname="Gibson" fullname="M Gibson">
      <organization>Nortel Networks</organization>
    </author>
    <date day="18" month="July" year="2000"></date>
    <abstract>
      <t>This draft describes the application of the COPS for Provisioning 
(COPS-PR) protocol for managing MPLS and its traffic engineering 
functionality. A new COPS client type is described, the COPS-MPLS 
client type, and the use of the basic COPS messages by this client 
type is described.

	 </t>
